						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #000016;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												<DIV>Not long ago there was a statement made that "our nerfing days are behind us". We all knew that this would not last long and here is the proof.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>King Stormhammer of Kaladim&nbsp;used to give great Ring of Scale faction. In fact about 7 kills would take you from max KoS to max Ally. He had a fast respawn time too which made Ring of Scale faction fairly easy to get.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now that VP has great quests that require Ring of Scale faction, King Stormhammer was NERFED to provide only a tiny faction hit. Even MM was nerfed so that now about 15 hours of AE killing the entire zone is required to max faction for Ring of Scale.&nbsp;Needless to say, this zone is now camped around the clock. The only other place to get faction is killing all the bards but that would take forever.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>King Stormhammer is a mob that has been in the game since it went live. He has always given great RoS faction. How would you characterize this change as anything but a nerf? Was the original faction "not intended"? Did you only happen to notice this recently? No. This was a nerf to prevent players from getting Ring of Scale faction.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And how exactly do you expect thousands of EQ players get Ring of Scale faction now?</DIV>
																		
