												i think the worst part of all this is that at lvl 20 and 25 newbies are advised to go to mistmore.  believe it or not, there really are some newbies left, i was kinda surprised to.<br>so nearly every one of them that shows up in mistmore is steamrolled within the first 10 seconds by a train of 60 mobs being pulled for an ae faction kill.  the hardier ones that manage to form groups either find that there are no mobs up for them to kill, or eventually one mob gets to close to an ae pull and they get steamrolled again.  who comes up with this stuff?  whos idea was it to make factioning require wiping newbie zones where people can actually get exp and maybe have some fun clean?  sure its funny to watch a couple lvl 20s get womped in .2 seconds by an ae pull offtracked temporarily the first couple times, but after that you have to start to feel kinda sorry for them.<br>this same thing happened in lower guk with the woodelf crown until some magnificent genious (yes, im being serious) decided to put bigger faction hits on mobs in sebilis.  so all the lvl 60s farming the faction could go there and kill stuff, not train a boatload of newbies and maybe even get a tiny bit of exp to go along with it.  not to mention escaping the drudgery of just killing train after train after train of mob in 2 hits then waiting 20 minutes for repops and repeating.<br>so i guess what im trying to say is: "why not find a higher lvl zone that noone goes to and put bigger faction hits per mob there?"  i can think of a couple off the top of my head that would actually make sense: charasis (venril sathir's wife's grave, vs and the ros hated eachother right?), dragon necropolis (zlandicar was banished from the ros for eating dragons, he gives a hit but noone else in the zone does) im sure there are even better zones that im not thinking of.<br>either of those zones would be great though, noone ever goes there (except the occasional necro clearing out hs for paltry tribute loot), provide a minor challenge and some smally amount of exp/leadership exp while also providing a slight challenge, have tons of mobs to kill, and you wouldn't be training the snot out of any people legitemately hunting there.
																		
										</td></tr>
